cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the problem of multi-object tracking in a multi-camera system, which involves computer vision, machine learning, and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a graph-based optimization algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of appearance and motion features for similarity computation suggests the involvement of machine learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with multi-camera systems, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of tracking in robotics applications suggests the involvement of cs.RO (Robotics).
